INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('296', '1', '2010-05-20 10:21:46', '2010-05-20 10:21:46', '<h3>Definitions:</h3>\r\n<strong>The Competition</strong> - means the joint Unity / Raindance.tv competition to be held during 2010 in association with InterCasino\r\n\r\n<strong>Competition Partners</strong> - means any companies including but not limited to InterCasino, Unity, Raindance.tv Plc, British Independent Film Awards, Raindance Festivals, or any others who are acting on behalf in any aspect of this competition.\r\n\r\n<strong>Competition Website</strong> - means the web pages hosted by Raindance.tv at http://raindance.tv/extraordinary for the purposes of promoting and operating the Competition, and the microsite http://welcometotheextraordinary.com which includes an iframe hosted by Raindance.tv to enable competition submissions.\r\n\r\n<strong>Entrants</strong> - means any person or persons who intend to or who have submitted a film for the Competition.\r\n\r\n<strong>Submitted Film</strong> - means any film entered for the Competition.\r\n\r\n<strong>End Title Card</strong> - means the JPEG image available via the Competition Website and which incorporates the Competition Partner Logos and Tag Lines.\r\n\r\n<strong>Partner Logo</strong> - means any marks or branding owned by InterCasino, Raindance, Unity and their affiliates.\r\n\r\n<strong>Tag Line</strong> - means the phrase “Welcome to the Extraordinary”\r\n<h3>Section 1</h3>\r\n1. This Competition is starting from May 24 2010\r\n\r\n2. The closing date for receipt of entries is July 25 2010. Entries must be submitted in the formats prescribed by Raindance.tv by using the upload function provided.\r\n\r\n3. There is no limit as to the number of Submitted Films each user can submit\r\n\r\n4. Films over 40 seconds in length in length will be disqualified.\r\n\r\n5. This Competition is free of charge and without purchase necessary, and is open to anyone who is resident in the world, who is 16 years of age or older, except employees of the Competition Partners, their agencies and anyone else connected with the creation and administration of the promotion.\r\n\r\n6. Submitted Films can be filmed and edited in any format, however, on request Entrants must be able to provide a high resolution copy of their film.\r\n\r\n7. Entrants must provide all additional data about themselves as required by Raindance.tv during the process of submitting their film.\r\n\r\n8. By registering for the competition, Entrants agree for their email address to be use to create a free account on Raindance.tv\r\n\r\n9. By submitting a film Entrants agree to the Competition terms and conditions when registering for the Competition.\r\n\r\n10. Entrants must ensure that they obtain all rights and clearances necessary to allow the film to be used as defined in clause 27 and that they obtain a signed release form from every person who appears in or contributes to the their Submitted Film. Raindance.tv and InterCasino reserve the right to request to see these forms.\r\n\r\n11. InterCasino has the right, once the Competition is over, to demand that you remove the End Title Card from your Film in any future use of it. You acknowledge this right and undertake to comply with it.\r\n\r\n12. There will be 1 winner of the main prize and 1 winner of the YouTube prize. These will be selected from films shortlisted by the jury INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('297', '1', '2010-05-20 10:21:06', '2010-05-20 10:21:06', 'Raindance Film Competition Terms and Conditions\n\nDefinitions:\nThe Competition - means the joint Unity / Raindance.tv competition to be held during 2010 in association with InterCasino\n\nCompetition Partners - means any companies including but not limited to InterCasino, Unity, Raindance.tv Plc, British Independent Film Awards, Raindance Festivals, or any others who are acting on behalf in any aspect of this competition. INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('298', '1', '2010-05-20 10:21:46', '2010-05-20 10:21:46