INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('378', '1', '2010-05-24 15:26:55', '2010-05-24 15:26:55', 'Born in 1978 in a village in south Lincolnshire Mathew Horne studied A level performing arts at Southwell Minster School and later gained a degree in drama from the University of Manchester.\r\n\r\nHorne began his career as a stand up  comedian and was spotted during the 2000 Edinburgh festival by Catherine Tate whom he later performed with on the popular comedy series the Catherine Tate Show. Performing in a wide variety of roles since including the hit series Teachers, the Roman Empire and in the second series of the BBC’s Robin Hood, he later starred in the film Lesbian Vampire Killers.\r\n\r\nOn 18 February 2009 he presented the Brit Awards alongside James Corden and Kylie Minogue. Together with Corden, he later presented the NME Shockwaves Awards and a section of Comic Relief in March 2009.\r\n\r\nDespite all these achievements, Mathew is perhaps best known for his leading role in the hugely popular, Bafta award winning romantic comedy sitcom, Gavin and Stacey where he plays 28 year old Billericay (Essex) based Gavin Shipman who begins a long distance relationship with Stacey West – based in Barry, near Cardiff.\r\n\r\nMathew Horne has now joined forces with Raindance, the UK’s largest independent film organisation, in a search for new international filmmaking talent.  The<em> Welcome to the Extraordinary</em> film competition, sponsored by InterCasino, the world’s first online casino, will showcase a new generation of filmmakers by inviting them to submit a short film bringing to life their expression of ‘the extraordinary’.\r\n\r\nActor Mathew Horne commented: “I’m really passionate about the idea of giving aspiring filmmakers a platform such as this to break into the industry.  I was lucky enough to launch my acting career back in 2003 and it’s great to now be helping to showcase new talent in this way.”\r\n\r\n“Getting your film screened at the Raindance Film Festival is a really extraordinary opportunity and I’m very excited about taking a look at the short films that are entered into the competition.”', 'Mathew Horne', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '305-revision-5', '', '', '2010-05-24 15:26:55', '2010-05-24 15:26:55', '', '305', 'http://staging.welcometotheextraordinary.com/2010/05/305-revision-5/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
